      <scopecontent id="aspace_fb2f0c98e34c8494d11fc7afcfb049d3">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Shipping and business records make up the papers of Samuel C. Johnson (1792-1872) of Guilford, Connecticut. The papers, which include bills, orders, receipts, invoices, inventories, and other financial and legal papers, detail goods and prices for shipments of merchandise on the sloop <title render="italic">
               <part>Clarissa</part>
            </title> sailing out of Naugatuck and Guilford under Captain Isaac Meigs, as well as other business transactions carried on by Johnson. The papers are arranged in chronological order.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
